{"vocabInfos":[{"lsjDefs":"<b> λουτρόν</b>, τό, <br /> in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] always <b>λοετρόν</b>, but <i>contraction</i> form in [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “hymnus ad Cererem” 50, 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus “Opera et Dies” 753 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; <i>Doric dialect</i> <b>λωτρόν</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus \">Refs 5th c.AD+</a>]: (λούω):— <b>bath, bathing-place</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Homerus Epicus, always in _plural_, θερμὰ λοετρά\">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>] hot <b>bath</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 22.444, +others; later θερμὰ λουτρά 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Choephori” 670, 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Trachiniae” 634 (Lyric poetry), CratesCom. 15, etc.; θερμὰ Νυμφᾶν λουτρά 5th c.BC: Pindarus Lyricus “O.” 12.19; also called Ἡράκλεια λουτρά 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Nubes” 1051; λοετρὰ Ὠκεανοῖο 8th c.BC: Ilias Homerus Epicus “Illiad” 18.489, 8th c.BC: Odyssea Homerus Epicus “Odyssey” 5.275 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]; σίτοισι καὶ λουτροῖσι in matters of eating and <b>washing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Herodotus Historicus 6.52; λουτρῷ χρωμένους 1st-2nd c.AD: Plutarchus Biographus et Philosophus 2.1109b: _sing._ first in 8th-7th c.BC: Hesiodus Epicus [same place]; τραπέσθαι πρὸς τὸ λ. 5th-6th c.BC: Plato Philosophus “Phaedo” 115a, compare 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Oeconomicus” 9.7 \">Refs 8th c.BC+</a>]: in <i>plural</i>, <b>bathing-establishment</b>, τὰ δημόσια λ. [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" “POxy.” 1252 B 22 (3rd c.AD), etc. \">Refs 3rd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level3><b>__2</b></Level3> <b>water for bathing</b> or <b>washing</b>, ὑδάτων ἐνεγκεῖν λουτρά [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Oedipus Coloneus” 1599 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; ἐν λουτροῖς while <b>bathing</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th-6th c.BC: Xenophon Historicus “Institutio Cyri (Cyropaedia)” 7.5.59 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λοῦσαί τινα λουτρόν give one a <b>bath</b>, wash one with water, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Antigone” 1201, 5th-6th c.BC: Aristophanes Comicus “Lysistrata” 469; λουτρὸν παρέχειν [prev. work] 377 \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]; λοῦσθαι λουτρόν <b>bathe</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 4th-5th c.BC: Aeschylus Tragicus “Fragmenta - American Journal of Philology” 366 (note); λουτρόν ἐστιν, οὐ πότος 2nd c.AD: Alexander Rhetor 9 \">Refs 4th c.BC+</a>]; νυμφικὰ λουτρά <b>the conveying of water to the bride</b> (compare λουτροφόρος), [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 2nd c.AD(?): Pollianus Epigrammaticus 3.43; in “NT”, of baptism, NT.Eph.5.26; λ. παλιγγενεσίας NT.Tit.3.5. \">NT+2nd c.AD+</a>]<br /><Level2><b>__II</b></Level2> in Poets, ={σπονδαί}, <b>libations to the dead</b>, [<a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" title=\" 5th c.BC: Sophocles Tragicus “Electra” 84, 434, 5th c.BC: Euripides Tragicus “Phoenissae” 1667, compare 5th c.AD(?): Hesychius Legal icographus see at {χθόνια λ}. \">Refs 5th c.BC+</a>]","strongNumber":"G3067","accentedUnicode":"λουτρόν","relatedNos":[{"strongNumber":"G3068","matchingForm":"λούω","stepTransliteration":"louō","gloss":"to wash","_zh_tw_Gloss":"洗淨了","_es_Gloss":"lavar","_zh_Gloss":"洗净了"}],"shortDef":"washing, bath","mediumDef":"washing, bath <br /><b>a bath, water for bathing; a bathing, washing, ablution,</b> <ref='Eph.5.26'>Eph. 5:26;</ref> <ref='Tit.3.5'>Tit. 3:5</ref>*","stepGloss":"washing","stepTransliteration":"loutron","count":2,"_es_Definition":"lavado, limpieza ; agua","_zh_tw_Definition":"沐浴, 洗滌","_zh_Definition":"沐浴, 洗涤","_step_Type":"word","_vi_Definition":"sự tắm rửa; lấy nước rửa","_zh_tw_Gloss":"洗, 洗滌","_es_Gloss":"lavamiento","_zh_Gloss":"洗, 洗涤"}]}